<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Questionable status. Mediterranean records are rare and considered questionable (
<bibRefCitation author="Giangrande, Adriana" journalOrPublisher="Atti della Societa Toscana di Scienze Naturali Memorie" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="153 - 189" title="Censimento dei policheti dei mari Italiani: Sabellidae Malmgren, 1867" volume="96" year="1989">Giangrande 1989</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Knight-Jones, Phyllis" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnaean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="385 - 467" title="A revision of Sabella, Bispira and Stylomma (Polychaeta: Sabellidae)" volume="123" year="1998">Knight-Jones and Perkins (1998)</bibRefCitation>
likewise consider Mediterranean specimens to belong to other species (e.g. the record by 
<bibRefCitation author="Iroso, Isabella" journalOrPublisher="Pubblicazioni della Stazione Zoologica di Napoli" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="47 - 91" title="Revisione dei Serpulidi e Sabellidi del Golfo di Napoli" volume="3" year="1921">Iroso (1921)</bibRefCitation>
probably is a juvenile 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellidae" genus="Bispira" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bispira mariae" order="Sabellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="mariae">Bispira mariae</taxonomicName>
(Lo Bianco, 1893)) and restrict the distribution of the species to the wider Caribbean area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
